# health-impact-receipt.form - foods, substances, and preparation processes answer with bounded evidence

The health-impact receipt turns a practical question into an inspectable claim:
what can be said about this food, substance, or preparation process for this
exposure and population?

The receipt is not a medical authority. It is a gate. It keeps five outcomes
separate:

- benefit-supported;
- risk-supported;
- mixed;
- unknown;
- refused.

Unknown is a real answer. A mechanism, nutrient delta, or molecule-level
hypothesis can stay visible without becoming a health claim.

(health-impact-receipt

  (lineage
    (derives-from evidence-grounding.form whole-lifecycle-fitness.form value-execution-as-recipe.form)
    (runnable form/form-stdlib/health-impact-receipt.fk)
    (proof form/form-stdlib/tests/health-impact-receipt-band.fk)
    (claim-shape subject-exposure-preparation-evidence-safety-witness-verdict))

  (subject
    (kind food OR substance OR preparation-process)
    (canonical-id from-public-source-when-available)
    (label human-readable))

  (exposure
    (dose required)
    (route required)
    (frequency required)
    (population required)
    (stop-boundary required))

  (preparation
    (process required-for-preparation-claim)
    (source-trace required)
    (measured required)
    (composition-delta optional-but-at-least-one-delta-required)
    (contaminant-delta optional-but-at-least-one-delta-required)
    (bioavailability-delta optional-but-at-least-one-delta-required))

  (evidence
    (lanes measured-human clinical observational mechanistic composition unknown)
    (source-trace required)
    (outcome-trace required)
    (molecular cellular organism tracked-as-gates)
    (third-party required-for-human-benefit-support)
    (effect benefit OR risk OR mixed OR none))

  (safety
    (toxicity-trace required)
    (interaction-trace required)
    (adverse-event-trace required)
    (contaminant-safe required)
    (risk-boundary required)
    (stop-boundary required)
    (risk-observed verdict-signal))

  (witness-pack
    (composition e.g. USDA-FDC)
    (chemical e.g. PubChem-or-DSSTox required-for-substance-claim)
    (literature e.g. PubMed-or-ClinicalTrials)
    (safety e.g. openFDA-or-EPA))

  (verdicts
    benefit-supported
    risk-supported
    mixed
    unknown
    refused)

  (refusal-reasons
    malformed-receipt
    overbroad-health-claim
    unsupported-claim
    missing-subject
    missing-exposure-boundary
    missing-source-witness
    missing-evidence
    missing-safety-boundary
    missing-chemical-witness
    missing-preparation-boundary)

  (invariants
    (no-dose-no-health-claim)
    (no-population-no-health-claim)
    (preparation-is-a-transform-not-a-label)
    (mechanism-only-stays-unknown)
    (risk-can-stand-without-benefit)
    (benefit-plus-risk-is-mixed)
    (universal-health-claims-refuse)))

# SHIPPED
#
# `form/form-stdlib/health-impact-receipt.fk` carries the executable receipt
# and verdict policy. `form/form-stdlib/tests/health-impact-receipt-band.fk`
# proves eight claims three-way: food benefit, preparation benefit, substance
# benefit, risk-only, mixed benefit+risk, mechanism-only unknown, missing
# exposure refusal, and universal-health/cure refusal.
